# Horror Facts вҖ” Every Scream Has a Source

[Go]
[PostgreSQL]
[Docker]

A dark atmospheric web application that reveals the **true stories behind famous horror films**. Built with Go, PostgreSQL, and pure HTML/CSS templates.

---

## Features

- **65+ horror movies** вҖ” Russian and foreign, each with real-life facts
- **AI-powered search** вҖ” powered by DeepSeek via OpenRouter. If a movie is not in the database, AI generates the answer in the same format
- **Interactive horror map** вҖ” real-world locations that inspired famous films
- **User authentication** вҖ” registration, login, JWT tokens, cookie-based sessions
- **Dark atmospheric UI** вҖ” custom glassmorphism design with noise texture and vignette
- **Clean architecture** вҖ” Go templates, repository pattern, middleware

---

## Tech Stack

| Layer | Technology |
|-------|-----------|
| Backend | Go (net/http, html/template) |
| Database | PostgreSQL 16 |
| AI | DeepSeek (via OpenRouter API) |
| Auth | JWT (golang-jwt) + bcrypt |
| Frontend | Tailwind CSS, vanilla JS |
| DevOps | Docker, Docker Compose |

---

## Quick Start

### Prerequisites

- Go 1.21+
- Docker & Docker Compose

### Setup

```bash
git clone https://github.com/V-SemYo/horror-facts.git
cd horror-facts
cp .env.example .env
# Edit .env вҖ” add your OpenRouter API key and JWT secret
docker-compose up -d
go run main.go
Open http://localhost:8080 вҖ” enter the void.

Environment Variables
Variable	Description	Default
DB_HOST	PostgreSQL host	127.0.0.1
DB_PORT	PostgreSQL port	5433
DB_USER	Database user	horror
DB_PASSWORD	Database password	вҖ”
DB_NAME	Database name	horror_facts
SERVER_PORT	HTTP server port	8080
JWT_SECRET	Secret key for JWT tokens	вҖ”
OPENROUTER_API_KEY	API key for AI search	вҖ”


Project Structure
text
horror_facts/
в”ңв”Җв”Җ main.go
в”ңв”Җв”Җ handlers/
в”ңв”Җв”Җ templates/
в”ңв”Җв”Җ static/
в”ңв”Җв”Җ internal/
